column4: Wanna see my stamp collection?  I don't have them here, but I have pictures of them on my phone.

column2: Do these pants make me look fat?
column3: I don't want to rain down on you with praises here, but you look like you've lost some weight!
column4: I had to bathe outside under the leaky gutter this morning because my bathroom is broken.

column2: What's your plan?
column3: This time I'm going to opt for something a lot more comfortable.
column4: I don't live a lavish lifestyle, but my boyfriend put the most expensive platinum ring on layaway.

column2: You're just in time...
column3: They gave me the latest iteration of the new item we'll be selling. I couldn't stop playing with it.
column4: Did you know that the change in our cafeteria food was a direct result of all of my complaints?

column2: Is that new?
column3: It's brand spankin' new!  Absolutely pristine, isn't it?
column4: I just got this flavored red lipstick!  You guys want to smell the cap?

column2: Do you know what that means?
column3: I think we're closer to understanding.  Every time we peel off a layer, there's another one waiting.
column4: I would eat fried rice, but I hate scallions.  Now I don't know what to do for lunch.

column2: Is it cold in here or is it just me?
column3: It is.  Care to go double or nothing on whether or not Ryan still shows up in flip flops?
column4: I think I'm going to invest the winnings from my lottery ticket into a bunch more tickets.

column2: I've been thinking about getting a different job...
column3: Are you in a hurry?  How actively are you looking?
column4: Don't all come at once, but I brought some homemade pecan pie!

column2: What do you think of our new hours?
column3: I was looking for more hours, not a cutback.  I suppose I'm happy they didn't cut me.
column4: If you're hungry, I can break off some of this homemade pumpkin bread for you.

column2: Should I run to the store at lunch?
column3: I give up!  Just go...I'll hold down the fort here.
column4: I got in trouble for not charging that cute guy yesterday.  Now, I can't offer any more discounts.

column2: Wow, that's mean!
column3: What?!  It's not like I called her fat!
column4: I dropped my purse 3 times on my way to work this morning.  You'd think it was made out of grease!

column2: Can I borrow a stapler?
column3: I don't want to get all of my things mixed up with yours.  Can you get your own?
column4: Check out this picture of a braid I did for my daughter's friend.  I even wove in feathers!

column2: Can I borrow some paper?
column3: How many trees are you gonna' murder over there?!  How about you use the back of your last piece!
column4: My abs are killing me!  I did crunches for the first time in years this morning.

column2: I can't wait for this Friday!!!
column3: I know!  It's been so long since I've been camping.  I need to get all of my things ready to go!!
column4: I can't seem to fit all of these pens into this mug.  Can one of you two help me out here?

column2: What's your favorite Superhero trait?
column3: Can you imagine being able to soar with the birds?
column4: I just bought tickets to Hawaii for Christmas - it'll be so much warmer than here!!!

column2: So, what's the verdict?
column3: I think she's going to stop saying all of those mean things to me.
column4: I absolutely love to watch pro wrestling!  Have you heard all their trash talking?!  Hilarious!

column2: Did you hear the news?
column3: Ya.  It looks like the last of our favorite shows was cancelled.
column4: Did you know that the they cut 5 sales positions on Monday?

column2: What have you decided?
column3: I'm going to send the pizza via mail.  They allow you to send food, don't they?
column4: Have you guys seen the movie "Titanic"?  It's such a good love story.  It reminds me of...

column2: What was your least favorite part?
column3: Not to avoid the question, but why don't we talk about something else.
column4: Don't forget about my party tomorrow!  It seems like you're were dodging my emails!

column2: Can I tell you something?
column3: Don't tell me you asked her out and she said no.  Swing and a miss!  2 more and you're out!
column4: I'm sorry for hitting you so hard on the shoulder earlier.  I was just trying to be playful.

column2: Can you believe she said that?
column3: So gross!  Why would we care if her belly button lint stinks?  Seriously?!?!
column4: These glasses make everything a blur.  Do either of you have any cleaner?

column2: Are you going to the party tonight?
column3: I didn't bring the right clothing for a pool party.
column4: Bob, that's quite the ensemble - are you going to an interview?

column2: Can you smell that?
column3: It's so stinky!  It's like every sheep in the world on a 95 degree day made into one air freshener!
column4: How much money do you guys make before they take out taxes?

column2: Are you getting that promotion?
column3: Probably not.  I didn't get my 40 in last week and they look at that kind of stuff.
column4: Is it 1PM or 2PM?  My watch is broken.

column2: You're just in time...
column3: I got up about 45 minutes ago and got here on time!  I even had time to make a breakfast burrito!
column4: I had a bagel in my fridge this morning...and carrots!

column2: I've been thinking about getting a different job...
column3: Did you look at the job postings online?  Is there anything that looks appealing on the list?
column4: Have you guys gotten paid yet today?  They usually do direct deposit, but didn't this time.

column2: Can I ask you a question?
column3: Take advantage of the opportunity!  I was just getting ready to head out for lunch.  Make it quick!
column4: I don't know if it will help any, but I have some free time if either of you need a hand.

column2: What do you think of our new hours?
column3: The option to work night shift was a good overture, but I'm going to stick with my current hours.
column4: I propose that we all swap lunches today.  I'm just so tired of bologna sandwiches.
